This paper deals with secure multi-party computation and machine learning, which are both topics that fall under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on training linear models, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). The system design and implementation aspects of the paper also suggest that it could belong to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy concerns, which could place it under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses information theory and coding, which could make it relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT).
